<div class="quiz-block" id="quiz">
    <h2>KNOWLEDGE CHECK</h2>
    <p class="quiz-intro">Ten questions. Select one answer per question. Feedback is immediate; score appears when all ten are answered.</p>

    <div class="quiz-q"><p><strong>Q1.</strong> The three defining changes from traditional GEO spacecraft manufacturing to LEO mass production are:</p>
        <div class="quiz-options">
            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="1" data-correct="false">A — Cheaper materials, smaller satellites, shorter orbits</button>
            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="1" data-correct="true">B — Design for manufacturability, automated assembly, and statistical process control replacing unit-level acceptance testing</button>
            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="1" data-correct="false">C — More satellites, lower orbits, faster computers</button>
            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="1" data-correct="false">D — Longer design life, more features, higher EIRP</button>
        </div><div class="quiz-feedback" id="fb1"></div></div>

    <div class="quiz-q"><p><strong>Q2.</strong> Statistical process control replaces 100% unit-level acceptance testing in mass satellite production because:</p>
