            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="2" data-correct="false">A — SPC is mandated by satellite regulations</button>
            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="2" data-correct="true">B — A process in statistical control produces predictably in-specification units — only a sample needs to be tested to confirm the process remains in control</button>
            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="2" data-correct="false">C — Unit-level testing is technically impossible at high production rates</button>
            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="2" data-correct="false">D — SPC catches more defects than unit testing</button>
        </div><div class="quiz-feedback" id="fb2"></div></div>

    <div class="quiz-q"><p><strong>Q3.</strong> COTS electronic components are viable for LEO broadband satellites below ~600 km but not for GEO because:</p>
