            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="3" data-correct="false">A — COTS components are too large for LEO satellites</button>
            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="3" data-correct="true">B — The radiation environment below ~600 km is significantly less severe than at GEO (inside the outer Van Allen belt at 35,786 km)</button>
            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="3" data-correct="false">C — COTS components run at lower voltage than rad-hard parts</button>
            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="3" data-correct="false">D — LEO satellites have larger solar arrays that shield electronics from radiation</button>
        </div><div class="quiz-feedback" id="fb3"></div></div>

    <div class="quiz-q"><p><strong>Q4.</strong> At a 20% learning rate, the cost of the 100th satellite relative to the first is approximately:</p>
