            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="4" data-correct="true">B — 46%</button>
            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="4" data-correct="false">C — 20%</button>
            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="4" data-correct="false">D — 1%</button>
        </div><div class="quiz-feedback" id="fb4"></div></div>

    <div class="quiz-q"><p><strong>Q5.</strong> A 5-year satellite design life is commercially rational for a LEO broadband constellation because:</p>
        <div class="quiz-options">
            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="5" data-correct="false">A — Technology cannot yet achieve longer LEO lifetimes</button>
            <button class="quiz-opt" data-q="5" data-correct="true">B — The replacement cadence is manageable at fleet scale, short design lives enable rapid technology refresh, and propellant budgets remain modest</button>
